d in the face of urgent medical and psychiatric needs. Kupers criticizes the physical and psychological abuse of prisoners and then offers rehabilitative alternatives to supermax isolation. Solitary is a must-read for anyone interested in understanding the true damage that solitary confinement inflicts on individuals living in isolation as well as on our society as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aPrisonersxMental healthzUnited States. 0aSolitary confinement - United States - Psychological aspects. 0aSolitary confinementzUnited StatesxPsychological aspects. 4aamerican penal system. 4abroken men. 4adangers of solitary confinement. 4aemotionally unstable. 4ahuman rights. 4ajudges. 4alaw. 4alawyers. 4aprison system. 4apsychiatric symptoms. 4apsychologist. 4asensory deprivation. 4asolitary confinement. 4aunfairly imprisoned. 4awindowless cell. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Forensic Psychology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520965737423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520965737.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles